      "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
      "identifier": "contract_declaration_style_drift",
      "summary": "The contracts package uses inconsistent construction patterns for equivalent catalog entries, which weakens architectural coherence.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`protocol_contracts.go` routes entries through `protocolActionContract(...)` and namespace/action helpers.",
        "`startram_contracts.go` builds `contractCatalogEntry` inline with hard-coded structure and does not reuse the same entry-construction path.",
        "Both files publish package-level contract IDs as `var`, mixing mutable-looking identifiers with immutable contract semantics."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Standardize one declaration pipeline for all contract families (e.g., a shared builder/registry helper), and make contract IDs immutable by construction where possible; this should be applied across both files so new contract families follow one architectural convention.",
